<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="208" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,463,332,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The fumose area on the apex of the wing make this species distinctive in both sexes, the cerci are extremely long and narrow, the surstyli are very rudimentary, the phallus has 2 very distinct long medial spurs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1037,439,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,464]" box="[199,1037,439,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,439,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Etymology.</emphasis>
